OL,3,CBoy, 12, becomes youngest to be
OL,4,Csentenced for Southport riots
OL,6,FA 12-year-old boy who threw stones at
OL,7,Fpolice outside a mosque in Southport
OL,8,Fis believed to have become the
OL,9,Fyoungest person sentenced after this
OL,10,Fsummer's disorder.
OL,12,FThe boy appeared accompanied by his
OL,13,Ffather at Liverpool Youth Court having
OL,14,Fpreviously admitted at an earlier
OL,15,Fhearing a charge of violent disorder
OL,16,Fon 31 July.
OL,18,FDistrict Judge Wendy Lloyd gave the
OL,19,Fyoungster a 12-month referral order, a
OL,20,Fthree-month curfew order and his
OL,21,Ffather a six-month parenting order.
